  "text": "Insensitivity to scope [CITATION_1] refers to the phenomenon where the subjective value given to a consequence is insensitive to the magnitude of this consequence. A similar effect is the range insensitivity phenomenon studied in the weighting of multiple criteria [CITATION_2] . These phenomena can interplay with the order effects mentioned in the previous section. For example, the modeling team may give too much attention to non-essential issues that were considered early in the modeling process.",
